data.title: Benefits Planner: Retirement
data.meta_description: If you were born in 1960 your full retirement age is 67. Find out how your Social Security benefits will be affected based on when you begin receiving benefits.
data.text:
You can start your Social Security retirement benefits as early as age 62, but the benefit amount you receive will be less than your full retirement benefit amount.

The chart below provides examples of the percentage of your full retirement benefit amount you and your spouse would receive from age 62 up to your full retirement age.

How Your Social Security Benefit Is Reduced
